              "free_text": [
                "",
                " Protons were detected in high resolution E-dE",
                "  telescopes. The dE detectors consisted of 2.0 mm",
                "  thick NE102A plastic scintillators. The E detectors",
                "  were CsI(Tl) scintillation crystals 7.61 cm in",
                "  diameter and 7.61 cm in length.",
                "The neutron energy was measured by a time-of-flight",
                " (TOF) method where the typical flight distances were",
                " about 7 m. The neutron detector consisted of an array",
                " of ten BC400 plastic scintillator bars, with",
                " dimensions 1.5 m x 0.15 m x 76 mm (thick), which were"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COINC",
                "EDE",
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Direct measurement."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The exclusive 16O(G,PN)14N-0,1,2,... reaction was",
                " measured for the photon energy range E(G) = 98.5 -",
                " 141.0 MeV with an excitation energy resolution of 2.8",
                " MeV. Protons were detected at 76 and 82 degrees and",
                " coincident neutrons were detected at the opening",
                " angle for quasifree deuteron photodisintegration.",
                " Only the T = 0, 1+, 3.95 MeV state in the residual",
                " 14N nucleus was significantly populated.  This",
                " corresponds to a preferred l = 0 angular momentum",
                " transfer to the recoil as is expected for quasifree",
                " kinematics. The absence of significant population  to",
                " other discrete states is evidence that absorption on",
                " correlated proton-neutron pairs with an angular",
                " momentum transfer of l >= 2 is largely suppressed for",
                " the low recoil momentum range of the current",
                " measurement.  As a consequence of this fact, and the",
                " absence of unnatural parity states, only absorption",
                " on proton-neutron pairs in relative motion l = 0, 2",
                " is expected for all possible shell model coupling. No",
                " significant population of the T = 1 state at 2.31 MeV",
                " is consistent with previous measurement demonstrating",
                " that absorption on proton-neutron pairs in an isospin",
                " triplet is suppressed. The results of the measurement",
                " to discrete states in the residual 14N nucleus are",
                " compared to microscopic calculations which include",
                " contributions above that the mean field due to the",
                " short range and tensor parts of the nuclear",
                " potential. Clear separation in the contribution of",
                " (1p)**-2 and (1p)**-1 (1s)**-1 continuum above 20 MeV",
                " indicates that absorption on l = 1 nucleon pairs is",
                " also important near quasifree kinematics."
              ]
            }
          ],
